<br>
I'm using <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm41.showMessage?topicID=6.topic">Rombus' Advanced UI</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> as a base for my setup, and I like it a lot... but for my paladin and ranger, I'd really like to have the stamina bar as well. Thing is, because they're hybrids, I can't simply <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm41.showMessage?topicID=287.topic">ditch the mana bar</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> in favour of the stamina bar. So I went in search of a player window that fulfilled my needs.<br>
<br>
I found what I was looking for packaged with <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqinterface.com/sdownload/fileinfo.php?id=542">this skin</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> (which can be seen <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqinterface.com/sdownload/preview.php?id=542">here</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->... the player window is in the top right corner). My only problem is that it's a bit too big. It would actually be the perfect size if I could cut the surname and shrink the first name of the character, just like Rombus did in his UI. So I went to Rombus' player window file and found this bit of code:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE CODE START--><pre> &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &lt;Label item =&quot;Player_NameTag&quot;&gt;
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &lt;ScreenID&gt;NameTag&lt;/ScreenID&gt;
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &lt;EQType&gt;1&lt;/EQType&gt;
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &lt;Font&gt;2&lt;/Font&gt;
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &lt;RelativePosition&gt;true&lt;/RelativePosition&gt;
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &lt;Location&gt;
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &lt;X&gt;4&lt;/X&gt;
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &lt;Y&gt;0&lt;/Y&gt;
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &lt;/Location&gt;
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &lt;Size&gt;
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &lt;CX&gt;145&lt;/CX&gt;
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &lt;CY&gt;14&lt;/CY&gt;
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &lt;/Size&gt;
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &lt;Text&gt;0&lt;/Text&gt;
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &lt;TextColor&gt;
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &lt;R&gt;255&lt;/R&gt;
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &lt;G&gt;255&lt;/G&gt;
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &lt;B&gt;255&lt;/B&gt;
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &lt;/TextColor&gt;
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &lt;NoWrap&gt;true&lt;/NoWrap&gt;
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &lt;AlignCenter&gt;false&lt;/AlignCenter&gt;
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &lt;AlignRight&gt;false&lt;/AlignRight&gt;
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &lt;AlignLeft&gt;true&lt;/AlignLeft&gt;
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &lt;/Label&gt;
</pre><!--EZCODE CODE END--><br>
<br>
Beautiful! It's the code for shrinking the name and displaying the first name only! So I copy it into the new player window file and add this line to the bottom:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE CODE START--><pre> &lt;Pieces&gt;Player_NameTag&lt;/Pieces&gt;</pre><!--EZCODE CODE END--><br>
<br>
When I log in, lo and behold -- the name showed up exactly the way I wanted it to.<br>
<br>
The problem, then?<br>
<br>
The old name didn't go away.<br>
<br>
What I had was my first name placed over my full name, and since they were different sizes, it was quite unreadable. Now I don't need to read my own name, but with the old name still being there, it still took up the same amount of space as it did before, and the whole idea behind this was to make it <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>smaller</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
So, the question: how do I make my name not show up in the player window? Where is the line that does this?<br>
<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance for any help you can give me... I'd really like to get this working. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=luxum>Luxum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Dark Elf Admirer<BR>Juju Incantatrix</span><br>  Posts: 1587<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/26/02 12:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: playerwindow help</span><hr size=1> Well you need to find the spot where the tag for the original nametag is and comment it out, along with the screen piece.  I'd give you an example but &quot;html comments are not allowed&quot; /rude ezboard.  Basically you add an !--  and a --  inside the brackets at the beginning and end of the section you want to comment out.  For instance if i wanted to comment out Rombus' playername label i'd put a !-- directly behind the &lt;  that starts the tag <!--EZCODE CODE START--><pre> &lt;Label item =&quot;Player_NameTag&quot;&gt;</pre><!--EZCODE CODE END-->  and a -- directly in front of the tag that ends the section <!--EZCODE CODE START--><pre>  &lt;/Label&gt;</pre><!--EZCODE CODE END-->  Then do the same to the tag for the screenpiece.  Feel free to PM me if that makes no sense, i can email you a better explanation w/o ezboard overriding me.<br>
